  <brief_title>Spiration Valves Against Standard Therapy</brief_title>
  <acronym>VAST</acronym>
  <official_title>Safety and Effectiveness of the Spiration Valve System (SVS) in Air Leaks</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Spiration, Inc.</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Spiration, Inc.</source>
  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>Yes</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      VAST is a multicenter, prospective, randomized, controlled study designed to evaluate
      treatment of persistent air leak with the SVS as compared to standard chest tube drainage
      management and other standard-of-care interventions in the control group. Eligible subjects
      will be randomized to receive either Spiration Valves (investigational arm) or continue
      standard-of-care treatment (control arm). Once the air leak has resolved, Spiration Valves
      should be removed.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
