  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Subject has an air leak â‰¥ 100 mL/min, as measured by a digital thoracic drainage
             system (DTDS)

          -  Subject has air leak present on at least the 5th day following origination.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Subject has air leak only on forced exhalation or cough

          -  Subject has sepsis

          -  Subject has pneumonia

          -  Subject has Acute Respiratory Distress Syndrome (ARDS)

          -  Subject is not an appropriate candidate for, or unable to tolerate, flexible
             bronchoscopy procedures

          -  Subject has undergone a bone marrow transplant

          -  Subject has a primary pneumothorax

          -  Subject has undergone a prior intervention (including pleurodesis, surgery, blood
             patch, and pneumoperitoneum) or valve placement.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
